{{> infoHeader}}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{{title}}</title>
</head>

<body>

  <section class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-xl px-4 py-32 lg:flex lg:h-screen lg:items-center">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <h2
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-300 via-blue-500 to-purple-600 bg-clip-text text-3xl font-extrabold text-transparent sm:text-5xl">
          {{name}}

          <span class="sm:block"> Module </span>
        </h2>

        <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-xl sm:text-xl sm:leading-relaxed">
          Attackers are planning a <i class="text-sky-400/100">ransomware</i> attack on the city's hospital. Hundreds of
          important files and
          information
          of patients will come under the control of the cyber attackers if their plan succeeds and demand a ransom from
          the victims in the form of payment to restore access.
        </p>

        <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-xl sm:text-xl sm:leading-relaxed text-sky-400/100" style="margin-top: 20px;">
          You are tasked with preventing such attacks from occurring. But first, you need to learn some basics of
          ransomware.

        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">


          <a href="/game/ransomeware">
            <button class="cybr-btn">
              Play
              <span class="cybr-btn__glitch">Play_</span>
            </button>
          </a>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</body>

</html>
